He found that the length of the shadow was the same in both places, despite Alexandria being much further north.
Eratosthenes concluded that the Earth must be curved. He also calculated the circumference of the Earth, although his figure was out by about 20%.

output:

The pearl is a natural gem, formed in a mollusk by a grain of sand or
other irritant, which the mollusk coats with nacre.  Nacre is a
chalky substance which is deposited layer by layer on the irritant,
giving the pearl its characteristic luster.  The best pearls are
found in the Persian Gulf, and the Gulf of Manaar in India.  The
varieties are the pearl, the baroque, and the blister.  The pearl is
round and perfect; the baroque, or barrel pearl, is irregularly
shaped; the blister pearl has a depression in the center.  The best
pearls are white, but they are also found in pink, black, yellow,
and other colors.  The most famous pearl is the pearl of Allah,
which was given to the Shah of Persia by a Persian fisherman.  The
pearl is worn as a charm against evil, and is also used for
ornamental purposes.

instruction: Why can't bank use cash as capital as a buffer for potential losses?
output:
As I understand it, banks have to hold capital against potential losses. This means they have to keep a certain amount of cash on hand to cover losses.
But why can't they use cash as a buffer?
Let's say the bank holds $1000 in cash. Then, they make a loan to a customer for $1000. If the customer defaults, the bank loses $1000. But they already have $1000 in cash, so they don't have to worry about losses.
Why can't they do this? Why do they have to hold capital against potential losses?
banking capital
Joshua D.Joshua D.
You can, and banks do, hold cash as a buffer against losses. The problem is, if you hold too much cash, you're not lending it out to someone else. And if you're not lending it out, you're not earning interest on it.
Banks have to hold capital against potential losses, but they also have to earn a return on the capital they've got. If they held all their capital in cash, they'd have a lot of cash, but they'd earn no interest on it. So banks have to strike a balance between holding capital against potential losses, and having enough capital to lend out.
Banks typically hold a small amount of capital in cash, and the rest in other assets, like loans. The amount of capital they hold in cash is a tiny fraction of their total capital.
A bank has to have enough capital to cover its potential losses, but it also has to have enough capital to lend out. So banks have to strike a balance between holding capital against potential losses, and having enough capital to lend out.

Anytown Bank obtaining and using consumer reports in connection with any credit or insurance transaction that is not initiated by the consumer in order to make firm offers of credit or insurance is known as:

A. Approving
B. Counteroffering
C. Endorsing
D. Prescreening
E. None of the above
output:
## Answer

D. Prescreening

## Explanation

Anytown Bank is obtaining and using consumer reports in connection with any credit or insurance transaction that is not initiated by the consumer in order to make firm offers of credit or insurance. This is known as prescreening.

instruction: How to improve instance segmentation AP metrics with human knowledge
output:
Posted on 2022-08-04 2022-08-04 by Yiwei Zhang
Segmentation is an important and challenging task in computer vision. Instance segmentation is a special case of semantic segmentation, which aims to label each pixel with a class and an instance ID. In the past few years, instance segmentation has made significant progress thanks to the development of deep learning. However, the performance of current instance segmentation methods is still far from satisfactory. One of the reasons is that the metrics used to evaluate instance segmentation are not very good.
In this blog post, we will discuss why the current metrics are not good and propose a new metric that can better evaluate instance segmentation performance. We will also show how to use human knowledge to improve the performance of instance segmentation.
The current metrics
The most popular metric for evaluating instance segmentation is the Intersection over Union (IoU), which is defined as follows:
IoU = TP / (TP + FP + FN)
where TP, FP, and FN are the number of true positives, false positives, and false negatives, respectively.
The problem with IoU is that it is not very sensitive to small differences in segmentation accuracy. For example, if a model has an IoU of 0.9 and another model has an IoU of 0.8, it is not clear which one is better.
Another problem with IoU is that it is not very sensitive to large differences in segmentation accuracy. For example, if a model has an IoU of 0.9 and another model has an IoU of 0.7, it is not clear which one is better.
The Dice coefficient
The Dice coefficient is a more sensitive metric than IoU. It is defined as follows:
Dice = 2 * TP / (2 * TP + FP + FN)
where TP, FP, and FN are the number of true positives, false positives, and false negatives, respectively.
The Dice coefficient is more sensitive to small differences in segmentation accuracy than IoU. For example, if a model has a Dice coefficient of 0.9 and another model has a Dice coefficient of 0.8, it is clear that the first model is better.

instruction: explain TypeScript and Duck Typing
output:
# Duck Typing

Duck typing is a programming paradigm that allows objects to be treated as instances of an interface, even if they do not explicitly implement the interface. In other words, an object can be used as if it were an instance of an interface, even if it does not have all of the methods or properties defined by the interface.

This can be useful in certain situations, such as when you want to work with a library that provides a particular interface but does not provide an implementation of that interface. For example, you might want to use a library that provides a `Shape` interface, but the library does not provide an implementation of that interface. In this case, you could use duck typing to create your own implementation of the `Shape` interface and use that implementation with the library.

Duck typing can also be useful when you want to create a type-safe interface for an object that is not intended to be used as an interface. For example, you might have a class that represents a user, but you do not want to expose the user's private data to the outside world. In this case, you could create a type-safe interface for the user class that only exposes the public methods and properties of the user.

However, it is important to note that duck typing can also lead to code that is difficult to maintain and debug. For example, if you use duck typing to work with a library that provides an interface, but that library is later updated to provide a different interface, your code may no longer work correctly. Additionally, duck typing can make it difficult to understand the purpose of a particular object, as it can be used as an instance of any interface that provides the same set of methods and properties.

In summary, duck typing is a programming paradigm that allows objects to be treated as instances of an interface, even if they do not explicitly implement the interface. It can be useful in certain situations, such as when working with a library that provides a particular interface but does not provide an implementation of that interface. However, it can also lead to code that is difficult to maintain and debug.

He saw a secondhand car being worth $8000. He wants to keep his old car until he can buy the secondhand one.
He thinks he can save $1000 each month but the prices of his old
car and of the new one decrease of 1.5 percent per month.
Furthermore this percent of loss increases of `0.5` percent
Our man finds it difficult to make all these calculations.
Can you help him?
How many months will it take him to save up enough money to buy the car he wants,
and how much money will he have left over?
output:
A man has a rather old car being worth $2000.
He saw a secondhand car being worth $8000. He wants to keep his old car until he can buy the secondhand one.
He thinks he can save $1000 each month but the prices of his old car and of the new one decrease of 1.5 percent per month.
Furthermore this percent of loss increases of `0.5` percent
Our man finds it difficult to make all these calculations.
Can you help him?
How many months will it take him to save up enough money to buy the car he wants,
and how much money will he have left over?
This is a simple problem of compound interest.
First we calculate the value of the old car after `n` months.
Let `P` be the price of the old car, `q` be the price of the new car, `r` be the rate of depreciation and `t` be the time in months.
We have `P = 2000, q = 8000, r = 0.15, t = n`.
So, the value of the old car after `n` months is
`V(n) = P(1 + r)^n = 2000(1 + 0.15)^n`
Now we calculate the value of the new car after `n` months.
`V(n) = q(1 + r)^n = 8000(1 + 0.15)^n`
Now we can calculate the amount saved each month.
`S(n) = P - V(n) = 2000 - 2000(1 + 0.15)^n`
We can find the number of months `n` for which the amount saved each month is `1000`.
`1000 = 2000 - 2000(1 + 0.15)^n`
`1000(1 - 0.15)^n = 2000`
`1000(0.85)^n = 2000`
`1000(0.85)^n/2000 = 1`

In Wyoming, public nudity is generally illegal. A person can be arrested for public nudity in Wyoming, but only if they are also doing something else illegal at the same time.
Wyoming Statutes 6-11-102. Nudity in public.
(a) A person commits an offense if he appears in a public place:
(i) In a state of nudity; or
(ii) In a state of nudity with the intent to arouse or gratify the sexual desire of the person or of any other person.
(b) Subsection (a) of this section does not apply to:
(i) A child less than two (2) years of age;
(ii) An adult female breastfeeding her child;
(iii) An actor or actress in a play, motion picture, television or other entertainment production;
(iv) A model in a photograph or other pictorial representation; or
(v) A person engaged in an activity of a bona fide educational, medical, legal, governmental or scientific nature.
(c) A person convicted of violating subsection (a) of this section is guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine of not more than seven hundred fifty dollars ($750.00), imprisonment for not more than six (6) months, or both.
(d) As used in this section, “state of nudity” means the showing of the human male or female genitals, pubic area or buttocks with less than a fully opaque covering, the showing of the female breast with less than a fully opaque covering of any part of the nipple, or the showing of covered male genitals in a discernibly turgid state.

instruction: I have two remote Debian servers, A and B. How can I copy a directory of files at `~/Documents/training_results` existing on server A to the path `~/training_results` on server B? I have SSH access on my local laptop to each of the servers, but neither of the servers have SSH access to the other.
output:
I've tried to use rsync, but that requires SSH access on both servers.

I've also tried to use rsync and scp to try to copy the files from server A to my laptop and then copy them from my laptop to server B, but I don't think that's the most efficient way to do it.

Is there a way to do this?

Answer: You could use rsync, but you'll have to use a third server (or your laptop).

The rsync daemon can be started on the laptop, and then you can connect to it from both servers.

On the laptop, you would start rsync in daemon mode:

\begin{code}
rsync -a -D --rsh="ssh -l user" serverA:/home/user/Documents/training_results/ serverB:/home/user/Documents/training_results/
\end{code}

This will run rsync in daemon mode, and the `--rsh` option will specify the ssh command to use when connecting to the server.

The rsync daemon will then be listening on the localhost port 873, and both the serverA and serverB will be able to connect to it and copy the files.

instruction: What is a Dyson Sphere?
output:
A Dyson sphere is a hypothetical megastructure that encloses a star, capturing all or most of its energy output. The concept was first described by Freeman Dyson in 1960, as a way to address the problem of the sun’s limited lifetime. Dyson envisioned a structure made up of orbiting mirrors that would reflect sunlight back onto the Earth, keeping it warm long after the sun had died.
While Dyson’s original idea was based on mirrors, more modern versions of the concept involve the use of solar panels or other energy-collecting devices. A Dyson sphere could potentially provide an inexhaustible source of energy for a civilization, allowing it to continue to thrive even after its star had died.

How do I check my system drive for errors on Windows? The chkdsk command in Windows can be used to check the integrity of the file system on a drive and fix any errors that are found.
How do I check my system drive for errors on Windows? The chkdsk command in Windows can be used to check the integrity of the file system on a drive and fix any errors that are found. To run chkdsk, open a Command Prompt window and type the following command:
chkdsk /f C:
Where C: is the drive letter of your system drive. If you’re not sure which drive letter is your system drive, you can open File Explorer and look at the drive letter under “This PC.”
If you have multiple drives, you can also run chkdsk on a specific drive by using the /r option. For example, to run chkdsk on drive D:, you would type the following command:
chkdsk /r D:

-It can help to improve the overall performance of your computer by fixing any issues with your file system.

instruction:
You are given a paper citation, convert it to the requested citation style.

Chicago: Vaswani, Ashish, Shazeer, Noam, Parmar, Niki, Uszkoreit, Jakob, Jones, Llion, Gomez, Aidan N., Kaiser, Lukasz, and Illia Polosukhin. "Attention Is All You Need." arXiv, (2017). https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.1706.03762.
MLA:
output:
Vaswani, Ashish, et al. "Attention Is All You Need." 2017.
APA: Vaswani, A., et al. "Attention Is All You Need." 2017.


## Usage

```python
from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCitation, CitationStyle

tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('google/xlnet-base-cased')

model = AutoModelForCitation.from_pretrained('google/xlnet-base-cased')

style = CitationStyle.CHICAGO

model.convert(tokenizer('This is a test.'), style)

# Chicago: This is a test.
```

## Reference

The original code is based on [this repository](https://github.com/pytorch/fairseq/blob/master/examples/citation_style_translation/style_translation.py).

## What you'll need

- A web browser (Chrome or Firefox)
- A text editor (VS Code, Atom, or Sublime)
- A Terminal (Mac users)
- A GitHub account

## How to get started

1. Fork this repository.
2. Clone the repository to your computer.
3. Open the terminal and navigate to the repository folder.
4. Run `npm install`.
5. Run `npm run start`.
6. Navigate to `localhost:8080`.

### How to deploy

1. Navigate to the `deploy` folder.
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Run `npm run deploy`.
4. Go to the [deployed](https://fake-news-sentence-finder.herokuapp.com/) website.

### How to update

1. Navigate to the `deploy` folder.
2. Run `git pull`.
3. Run `npm install`.
4. Run `npm run deploy`.
5. Go to the [deployed](https://fake-news-sentence-finder.herokuapp.com/) website.

### How to test

1. Navigate to the `deploy` folder.
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Run `npm run test`.

## How to contribute

1. Fork this repository.
2. Clone the repository to your computer.
3. Create a branch.
4. Add your changes.
5. Run `npm install`.
6. Run `npm run test`.
7. Submit a pull request.

```
I'm trying to get a list of products that people who have visited this product might also be interested in.

\begin{code}

top_products = [product for product in products if common_word in product.name]
\end{code}

How can I get the top 100 most related products?

\begin{code}
https://webservices.amazon.com/onca/xml?Service=AWSECommerceService&Operation=ItemLookup&ItemId=<ASIN>

\begin{code}
```

```python
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
```

```python
instruction:
You should take the time to read the situation and problem carefully and give the best advice you can.

I'm roadtripping down New Zealand with a friend and he is driving me insane. He hasn't enjoyed all the tours we've been on and doesn't want to chat about ANYTHING. We're a week into our trip and this is the quietest I've ever been when hanging out with another person as he rebuffs all my attempts at conversation. He wears his airpods in the car and around the accommodation - not that I've kept trying to talk to him. Honestly, he is bringing some seriously bad vibes to everything and it's ruining my trip.
We don't have anything booked in yet for the South Island, so I'm planning to ditch him in Wellington at the ferry. Probably book my own car in Picton and just relax alone for the rest of the trip. (Just thinking about it is such sharp relief that it makes me feel emotional. I'll pay whatever price I have to just to get away from him.)
Obviously telling him he is ruining my trip with his negative energy isn't the best way to approach this.
Any advice for the best approach so we can split amicably? Or at least not have an argument that ends with very hurt feelings?
output:
Comment: You have a friend who is taking you on a trip. You are being ungrateful.

Comment: Why would you be paying extra money? Why not just split the costs of the trip?

Comment: @TheGreatDuck I didn't think about that! We're staying at his parents' place at the start and end of the trip, so I'll probably just pay for the ferry, and then I can just use my own car for the rest of the trip.

Comment: I'd be curious as to why he isn't enjoying the tours.  Are they too expensive?  Too boring?  Too long?  Too short?  What are they?  Are they the only things you are doing?  Do you have any activities together?  Have you asked him why he is so negative?  Have you asked him if there is anything you can do to improve the trip?  Have you asked him if he would like to change the trip?

Comment: @user2705196 He's an introvert and he just doesn't like crowds and being on tour buses. We've done some hiking together, but I have to be honest, I've been really selfish and haven't tried to include him much. I've asked him if he would like to change the trip and he said no, but I think I should have just asked him about it earlier.

Comment: @user2705196 I'll be honest, I'm pretty annoyed that I haven't been able to get him to enjoy anything so far, and I think that's coming through. I'm also really annoyed that he doesn't want to chat about anything.

Comment: If he is an introvert, then it's not necessarily your fault that he doesn't enjoy crowds.  I know that I'm an introvert, and I don't like crowds.  I also don't like being on tour buses.  If he is willing to change the trip, maybe you can find some things that you can both enjoy.

Comment: @user2705196 Thanks, I think you're right. I'm going to try and make the best of the rest of the trip.

instruction:
```
```
You are given some reviews for a movie. Each video might have mentioned some negative or positive points about the movie. Read them carefully and extract the positive and negative points mentioned in all of the reviews. Then, make a list of these points and summarize them as positive points and negative points.

Review 1: I'm not sure if it's just the fact that Ed Norton really grates on me in this film, but I never really bought into the idea of Fight Club being some kind of cultural phenomenon. Yes it's an innovative story, told via a strong script, engaging characters and intense cinematography. But is it really worthy of such high praise? Personally, I find it starts to fall apart halfway through and actually becomes quite tedious towards the end. Everything just becomes a little bit childish and contrived as the story loses touch with its base elements and the rage against the machine vibe takes over. I have huge respect for the way this film was made but, much like The Matrix, I feel like people attach way more importance to this movie than it deserves.
Review 2: The film tells the story of men who cannot adapt to the social order in today's world, under the leadership of Tyler Durden, to discover their natural instinct, masculinity, and to escape from their unhappy lives.
Review 3: Despite a good theme, great acting and important messages that this movie convey in an unorthodox way, I think it fails to connect the audience with the storyline and leaves him in a world of confusion. Although, majority of reviews find this movie entertaining and interesting, yet I would choose to be a minority that believes that this movie is extremely overrated.
Review 4: Is creating chaos, explosions and membership in a militant sect the way to get rid of material shackles ?! The visual effects are fascinating and the story is compelling until the second half. Unfortunately, it doesn't end well.
output:
## Input: 

A list of reviews, one per line.

## Output: 

A list of positive points and negative points, one per line.

## Example: 

```
input:

"I'm not sure if it's just the fact that Ed Norton really grates on me in this film, but I never really bought into the idea of Fight Club being some kind of cultural phenomenon. Yes it's an innovative story, told via a strong script, engaging characters and intense cinematography. But is it really worthy of such high praise? Personally, I find it starts to fall apart halfway through and actually becomes quite tedious towards the end. Everything just becomes a little bit childish and contrived as the story loses touch with its base elements and the rage against the machine vibe takes over. I have huge respect for the way this film was made but, much like The Matrix, I feel like people attach way more importance to this movie than it deserves."

"The film tells the story of men who cannot adapt to the social order in today's world, under the leadership of Tyler Durden, to discover their natural instinct, masculinity, and to escape from their unhappy lives."

"Despite a good theme, great acting and important messages that this movie convey in an unorthodox way, I think it fails to connect the audience with the storyline and leaves him in a world of confusion. Although, majority of reviews find this movie entertaining and interesting, yet I would choose to be a minority that believes that this movie is extremely overrated."

"Is creating chaos, explosions and membership in a militant sect the way to get rid of material shackles ?! The visual effects are fascinating and the story is compelling until the second half. Unfortunately, it doesn't end well."


output:

"Negative points: "

Table: Person

Table: Address
| Column Name | Type     |
| addressId        | int         |
| personId          | int         |
| city                   | varchar|
| state                | varchar |
addressId is the primary key column for this table.
Each row of this table contains information about the city and state of one person with ID = PersonId.
Write an SQL query to report the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table. If the address of a personId is not present in the Address table, report null instead.
Return the result table in any order.
Implementation:
select FirstName, LastName, City, State
from Person left join Address
on Person.PersonId = Address.PersonId

Summarize the article you have been given in a brief manner.

Mathematics and art are related in a variety of ways. Mathematics has itself been described as an art motivated by beauty. Mathematics can be discerned in arts such as music, dance, painting, architecture, sculpture, and textiles. This article focuses, however, on mathematics in the visual arts.
Mathematics and art have a long historical relationship. Artists have used mathematics since the 4th century BC when the Greek sculptor Polykleitos wrote his Canon, prescribing proportions conjectured to have been based on the ratio 1:√2 for the ideal male nude. Persistent popular claims have been made for the use of the golden ratio in ancient art and architecture, without reliable evidence. In the Italian Renaissance, Luca Pacioli wrote the influential treatise De divina proportione (1509), illustrated with woodcuts by Leonardo da Vinci, on the use of the golden ratio in art. Another Italian painter, Piero della Francesca, developed Euclid's ideas on perspective in treatises such as De Prospectiva Pingendi, and in his paintings. The engraver Albrecht Dürer made many references to mathematics in his work Melencolia I. In modern times, the graphic artist M. C. Escher made intensive use of tessellation and hyperbolic geometry, with the help of the mathematician H. S. M. Coxeter, while the De Stijl movement led by Theo van Doesburg and Piet Mondrian explicitly embraced geometrical forms. Mathematics has inspired textile arts such as quilting, knitting, cross-stitch, crochet, embroidery, weaving, Turkish and other carpet-making, as well as kilim. In Islamic art, symmetries are evident in forms as varied as Persian girih and Moroccan zellige tilework, Mughal jali pierced stone screens, and widespread muqarnas vaulting.

The "fair trade" movement, also known as the "trade justice" movement, promotes the use of labour, environmental and social standards for the production of commodities, particularly those exported from the Third and Second Worlds to the First World. Such ideas have also sparked a debate on whether trade itself should be codified as a human right.
output:
## Fair trade as a human right

### Arguments for fair trade as a human right

Fair trade, as an alternative to free trade, is often seen as an important step towards economic justice. Fair trade seeks to achieve social justice and sustainable development through the production and consumption of goods in a way that is socially responsible and environmentally sound. It promotes the rights of producers and workers to a fair wage and safe working conditions. It also promotes sustainability by encouraging the use of environmentally friendly practices in the production of goods. By providing access to markets and resources, fair trade helps to reduce poverty and inequality, and to promote economic development in the developing world.

### Arguments against fair trade as a human right

Opponents of fair trade as a human right argue that it is not a right but a privilege. They argue that the right to fair trade should be granted only to those who can demonstrate their ability to meet the requirements of fair trade. This could include having a certain level of economic development, a certain level of social and environmental responsibility, and a certain level of political stability. Opponents also argue that fair trade should not be seen as a right but rather as a privilege that is granted to those who can demonstrate their ability to meet the requirements of fair trade.

instruction:
Describe how to prepare the given food in your own words. Note down the ingredients you will need and the steps you will take to prepare them.

Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies
output:
### Ingredients

- 1/2 cup unsalted butter
- 1/4 cup granulated sugar
- 1/4 cup light brown sugar
- 1/2 teaspoon salt
- 2 eggs
- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
- 1/2 teaspoon baking soda
- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips

### Directions

1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
2. In the bowl of an electric mixer, beat the butter, sugars, and salt until light and fluffy.
3. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
4. In a small bowl, combine the flour and baking soda. Add to the butter mixture and beat until just combined. Stir in the vanilla.
5. Using a small spoon, drop the dough by the teaspoonful onto the prepared baking sheets.
6. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown around the edges. Cool on the baking sheets for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool completely.

### Notes

- This recipe makes about 4 dozen cookies.
- These cookies are delicious with a glass of cold milk.
- These cookies are best enjoyed within 3 days.

The Great Gatsby
output:
F. Scott Fitzgerald

To Myra

BOOK ONE

Chapter I

In my younger and more vulnerable years my father gave me some advice that I've been turning over in my mind ever since.
"Whenever you feel like criticizing any one," he told me, "just remember that all the people in this world haven't had the advantages that you've had."

He didn't say any more, but we've always been unusually communicative in a reserved way, and I understood that he meant a great deal more than that. In consequence I'm inclined to reserve all judgments, a habit that has opened up many curious natures to me and also made me the victim of not a few veteran bores. The abnormal mind is quick to detect and attach itself to this quality when it appears in a normal person, and so it came about that in college I was unjustly accused of being a politician, because I was privy to the secret griefs of wild, unknown men. Most of the con- men I met in prison professed to be very superior to me and one (a very important one) refused my friendship until I made the unqualified concession that he was a moral genius. I wasn't used to this kind of thing. I had a dim idea that American businessmen were accustomed to being morally superior to an employee, but I'd had very little experience. Now I began to feel the pressure of the popular conviction that the American businessman is a moral arbiter.

I was also very fond of the theatre. Men who had spent their entire lives in the East were surprised by the fact that I liked it so much. Even those who were from the Middle West shared this astonishment. I think they felt, or assumed, that I was showing off--as if I were an "easterner" newly arrived from New York. They used to snigger, "Theatrical?" and laugh very proudly at their provincialism--but I never cared. Dishonesty in a woman is a thing you never blame deeply--I was quite indignant. Based on the facts that have been provided, prove the following statement.

Statement: "For every integer k, k^2 + 2k + 1 ≥ 0"
Fact: The square of any real number is non-negative.
output:
Answer: Suppose $k = 0$. Then $k^2 + 2k + 1 = 0^2 + 2 \cdot 0 + 1 = 1 \geq 0$.

Suppose $k = 1$. Then $k^2 + 2k + 1 = 1^2 + 2 \cdot 1 + 1 = 4 \geq 0$.

Suppose $k = -1$. Then $k^2 + 2k + 1 = (-1)^2 + 2 \cdot (-1) + 1 = -2 + 2 + 1 = 1 \geq 0$.

Suppose $k = 2$. Then $k^2 + 2k + 1 = 2^2 + 2 \cdot 2 + 1 = 8 \geq 0$.

Thus, for every integer k, k^2 + 2k + 1 ≥ 0.

Comment: You can't use a join. The subquery returns a list of directors. You can only use a join to compare the values in two columns.

Comment: Ah I see, I thought it was a subquery and I didn't know how to use it to select the movie name.  Thank you.

Answer: You can use `JOIN` to join the `movie` table with the `director` table to get the movie names for each director:

\begin{code}
SELECT d.name, m.name
FROM director d
JOIN movie m ON d.id = m.director_id
WHERE d.name = 'Spike Lee'
\end{code}

Comment: I think this is the best answer because it will work for any director, not just Spike Lee.

Answer: \begin{code}
SELECT m.name
FROM movie m
JOIN director d ON d.id = m.director_id
WHERE d.name = 'Spike Lee'
\end{code}

Comment: `m.name` is not a column in `director`.

Comment: Thanks for pointing out that mistake. I have updated the answer.

Answer: \begin{code}
SELECT m.name
FROM movie m
JOIN director d ON d.id = m.director_id
WHERE d.name = 'Spike Lee'
\end{code}

I highly recommend that everyone take the time to check it out. The exhibit is a collection of prints from the artist’s 20 year career. The prints are a mix of his more famous pieces as well as some that are not so well known. The prints are hung in an order that I assume is meant to represent his career as an artist. It starts with his more “traditional” works and ends with his more experimental pieces. The prints are hung in a way that is very easy to view and the exhibit is not too large. It is also very well lit. The exhibit is located in the Harvard Square area of Cambridge, MA and it is open to the public. The exhibit is free, but donations are accepted. The exhibit is open from 10am to 6pm on weekdays and from 10am to 4pm on weekends. The exhibit will be open until October 31st.

Give a brief explanation of the requested part of the paper.

Paper: The dominant sequence transduction models are based on complex recurrent or convolutional neural networks that include an encoder and a decoder. The best performing models also connect the encoder and decoder through an attention mechanism. We propose a new simple network architecture, the Transformer, based solely on attention mechanisms, dispensing with recurrence and convolutions entirely. Experiments on two machine translation tasks show these models to be superior in quality while being more parallelizable and requiring significantly less time to train. Our model achieves 28.4 BLEU on the WMT 2014 English-to-German translation task, improving over the existing best results, including ensembles, by over 2 BLEU. On the WMT 2014 English-to-French translation task, our model establishes a new single-model state-of-the-art BLEU score of 41.8 after training for 3.5 days on eight GPUs, a small fraction of the training costs of the best models from the literature. We show that the Transformer generalizes well to other tasks by applying it successfully to English constituency parsing both with large and limited training data.

We present a state-of-the-art speech recognition system developed using end-to-end deep learning. Our architecture is significantly simpler than traditional speech systems, which rely on laboriously engineered processing pipelines; these traditional systems also tend to perform poorly when used in noisy environments. In contrast, our system does not need hand-designed components to model background noise, reverberation, or speaker variation, but instead directly learns a function that is robust to such effects. We do not need a phoneme dictionary, nor even the concept of a "phoneme." Key to our approach is a well-optimized RNN training system that uses multiple GPUs, as well as a set of novel data synthesis techniques that allow us to efficiently obtain a large amount of varied data for training. Our system, called Deep Speech, outperforms previously published results on the widely studied Switchboard Hub5'00, achieving 16.0% error on the full test set. Deep Speech also handles challenging noisy environments better than widely used, state-of-the-art commercial speech systems.Collapse

RoMQA: A Benchmark for Robust, Multi-evidence, Multi-answer Question Answering

Create a short, concise summary of the paper based on its abstract.

Few-shot learning (FSL) is one of the key future steps in machine learning and raises a lot of attention. In this paper, we focus on the FSL problem of dialogue understanding, which contains two closely related tasks: intent detection and slot filling. Dialogue understanding has been proven to benefit a lot from jointly learning the two sub-tasks. However, such joint learning becomes challenging in the few-shot scenarios: on the one hand, the sparsity of samples greatly magnifies the difficulty of modeling the connection between the two tasks; on the other hand, how to jointly learn multiple tasks in the few-shot setting is still less investigated. In response to this, we introduce FewJoint, the first FSL benchmark for joint dialogue understanding. FewJoint provides a new corpus with 59 different dialogue domains from real industrial API and a code platform to ease FSL experiment set-up, which are expected to advance the research of this field. Further, we find that insufficient performance of the few-shot setting often leads to noisy sharing between two sub-task and disturbs joint learning. To tackle this, we guide slot with explicit intent information and propose a novel trust gating mechanism that blocks low-confidence intent information to ensure high quality sharing. Besides, we introduce a Reptile-based meta-learning strategy to achieve better generalization in unseen few-shot domains. In the experiments, the proposed method brings significant improvements on two datasets and achieve new state-of-the-art performance.

instruction:
Someone gives you some information about where they want to go and what they enjoy seeing and doing. Describe a proper road trip for them and find the best stops and sctivities in the way.

I'm looking for a west coast road trip. My goal is to start near San Diego and travel to Los Angeles.
output:
I'd like to stop by the beach and take a hike or two.

# Challenge

Build a web application that can take in a user's location and a destination and find the best stops and activities along the way.

## Acceptance Criteria

* Users can input their starting location and destination
* Users can input the types of activities they'd like to do on the trip
* The application will generate a list of stops and activities along the way
* The application will include the distance and time it will take to get to the next stop
* The application will include a map of the route

# Hints

* You can use the Google Maps API to generate directions
* You can use the Google Places API to get information about places

# Test Scenarios

* User input San Diego as their starting location and Los Angeles as their destination
* User input "Beach" as one of the activities they want to do on their trip
* The application generates a list of stops and activities along the way
* The application includes a map of the route
* The application includes the distance and time it will take to get to the next stop

# Bonus

* User input "Hiking" as one of the activities they want to do on their trip
* The application generates a list of stops and activities along the way that include hiking
* The application includes the distance and time it will take to get to the next stop

# Notes

You may want to use a database to store your data so that it can be reused in subsequent trips.

# Resources

* [Google Maps API](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/tutorial)
* [Google Places API](https://developers.google.com/places/web-service/search)
* [Google Maps API Directions](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/directions)
* [Google Maps API Places](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/places)

```
instruction: Explain the process of gene editing using CRISPR-Cas9 technology, and discuss its potential applications and ethical implications.
output:
CRISPR-Cas9 is a gene editing technology that allows for precise and efficient modification of DNA sequences in living cells. This technology has the potential to revolutionize many fields of research and medicine, as well as raise ethical concerns. In this article, we will explore the process of CRISPR-Cas9 gene editing, its potential applications, and the ethical considerations that must be taken into account when using this technology.
The Process of CRISPR-Cas9 Gene Editing
The CRISPR-Cas9 system works by using a guide RNA (gRNA) to identify and target a specific sequence of DNA. Once the gRNA has bound to the target DNA, the Cas9 enzyme cuts the DNA at the target site, creating a double-stranded break. This break can then be repaired by the cell's natural DNA repair mechanisms, or by introducing new DNA into the cell.
This process can be used to delete, insert, or replace genes in the genome, as well as to modify specific regions of the genome. The CRISPR-Cas9 system is highly efficient and can be used to target multiple genes simultaneously.
Potential Applications of CRISPR-Cas9 Gene Editing
CRISPR-Cas9 has the potential to revolutionize many fields of research and medicine. For example, it can be used to study the function of specific genes, to develop new therapies for genetic diseases, and to create genetically modified organisms for use in agriculture and industry.
In medicine, CRISPR-Cas9 can be used to treat genetic diseases caused by mutations in specific genes. For example, it can be used to correct the mutations that cause sickle cell anemia or cystic fibrosis. It can also be used to treat cancer by targeting and deleting cancer-causing genes.
In agriculture, CRISPR-Cas9 can be used to create genetically modified crops that are more resistant to pests and diseases, or that have increased yields. It can also be used to create livestock that are more resistant to disease or that produce higher-quality meat.

instruction: How do vaccinations work to protect individuals and communities from infectious diseases, and what is herd immunity?
output:
Vaccinations are one of the most effective ways to prevent the spread of infectious diseases. Vaccinations work by introducing a small amount of a disease-causing microbe (such as a virus or bacteria) into the body. The vaccine contains a weakened or inactivated form of the microbe, which does not cause the disease but stimulates the immune system to produce antibodies and develop immunity against the disease.
Vaccinations have been responsible for the eradication of smallpox, the near eradication of polio, and the control of many other infectious diseases. By protecting individuals from these diseases, vaccinations also help to protect the broader community by reducing the spread of infection.
Herd immunity refers to the indirect protection that occurs when a significant proportion of a population is immune to a disease, making the spread of disease more difficult. When a high percentage of a population is immune to a disease, it becomes difficult for the disease to spread because there are fewer susceptible individuals to infect. This helps to protect those who cannot be vaccinated, such as young children and those with weakened immune systems.
Overall, vaccinations and herd immunity are important tools for preventing the spread of infectious diseases and protecting individuals and communities.

instruction: Explain the process of natural selection and how it contributes to the evolution and adaptation of species.
output:
Natural selection is a key concept in evolutionary theory. The theory of natural selection was first developed by Charles Darwin and Alfred Wallace in the 19th century and has since been refined and expanded upon by many other scientists.
Natural selection is the process by which individuals with certain traits are more likely to survive and reproduce, while individuals with different traits are less likely to survive and reproduce. Over time, this process can lead to the emergence of new species and the adaptation of existing species to new environments.
One of the key features of natural selection is that it is a gradual process. Individuals with a particular trait may have a slight advantage over others, but it may take many generations for that trait to become widespread in a population. This is because not all individuals with the trait will survive and reproduce, and some individuals without the trait may still be able to survive and reproduce.
Another important feature of natural selection is that it is non-random. Individuals with certain traits may have a greater chance of surviving and reproducing, but it is not a guarantee. For example, a lion with strong claws may be more likely to catch and kill its prey, but there is no guarantee that the lion will always be successful.
Natural selection also plays a role in adaptation. Individuals with traits that are well-suited to their environment are more likely to survive and reproduce, while individuals with less well-suited traits are less likely to survive and reproduce. Over time, this process can lead to the emergence of new species and the adaptation of existing species to new environments.
Natural selection is a key concept in evolutionary theory and has been studied extensively by scientists. It is a gradual and non-random process that can lead to the emergence of new species and the adaptation of existing species to new environments.
The process of natural selection can be explained as follows:
1. Overproduction: Organisms produce more offspring than can survive to reproduce.
2. Variation: Individuals within a population may have different traits, such as different sizes, shapes, and colors.
3. Selection: Individuals with certain traits may be better suited to their environment and have a greater chance of surviving and reproducing.
4. Heredity: Offspring inherit the traits of their parents

instruction: In a world where automation is becoming increasingly prevalent, is it more important to prioritize job creation or technological progress?
output:
There is no doubt that automation is becoming increasingly prevalent in today's world. With the advent of artificial intelligence and other cutting-edge technologies, machines are becoming more and more capable of performing tasks that were once thought to be exclusively the domain of humans.
This trend is having a profound impact on the job market, as it is leading to the displacement of workers in a wide range of industries. In response to this, some people are calling for a greater emphasis on job creation as a way to offset the negative effects of automation.
Others, however, argue that it is more important to prioritize technological progress, as this is what will ultimately lead to a better future for humanity. So, which is the right approach? Is it more important to prioritize job creation or technological progress?
There are certainly valid arguments on both sides of this debate. On the one hand, there is no doubt that automation is leading to job displacement, and that this is having a negative impact on many people's lives. As such, it is important to find ways to offset this impact, and one way to do this is to prioritize job creation.
```

d = √((8)^2 + (2)^2)
d = √(64 + 4)
d = √(68)
d = 8.318 units

Are you planning a trip to Hawaii and looking for some inspiration? Look no further! In this article, we will provide you with a comprehensive guide to planning the perfect Hawaiian vacation.
From exploring the stunning natural beauty of the islands to experiencing the unique culture and cuisine, there is something for everyone in Hawaii. We will cover everything from the best time to visit, to where to stay, what to do, and how to get around.
Whether you are a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler, this guide will help you plan a trip that you will never forget. So, grab your sunscreen and your sense of adventure, and let’s get started!
Hawaii is a group of islands located in the Pacific Ocean, and is part of the United States. It is known for its stunning natural beauty, with lush forests, stunning beaches, and active volcanoes.
The islands are home to a diverse array of cultures, with a mix of Hawaiian, Asian, and American influences. The climate is tropical, with warm temperatures year-round.
The best time to visit Hawaii is during the dry season, which runs from April to October. During this time, the weather is warm and sunny, with minimal rain.
However, Hawaii is a popular destination year-round, so it is possible to visit during the wet season as well. Just be aware that there may be more rain and cloud cover during this time.
There are several different islands in Hawaii, each with its own unique character and attractions. The most popular islands for tourists are Oahu, Maui, and the Big Island of Hawaii.
Oahu is home to the city of Honolulu and is known for its lively nightlife, shopping, and dining. Maui is known for its beautiful beaches, waterfalls, and hiking trails. The Big Island of Hawaii is known for its active volcanoes, waterfalls, and stunning landscapes.
Hawaii is a great destination for all types of travelers, from families to couples to solo travelers. There are a variety of activities to choose from, including hiking, snorkeling, surfing, and exploring the islands’ rich culture and history.
